      "span_text": "We see hints of this interactivity in the in vivo studies that shed some light on the process by which the patterning of one individual sparks the relational processing of others.  For instance, when a medical resident notes a particular anomaly in the symptoms of a patient, there is a greater likelihood that other residents will interject additional anomalies into the discussion."
